.SH NAME
sysfs_file_change_owner \- change owner of a sysfs file.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sysfs_file_change_owner
.BI "(struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "kuid_t kuid "  ","
.BI "kgid_t kgid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kobj" 12
object.
.IP "name" 12
name of the file to change.
.IP "kuid" 12
new owner's kuid
.IP "kgid" 12
new owner's kgid
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function looks up the sysfs entry \fIname\fP under \fIkobj\fP and changes the
ownership to \fIkuid\fP/\fIkgid\fP.

Returns 0 on success or error code on failure.
